---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="FAQ" description="Frequently asked questions about chiropractic care at The Bridge Chiropractic. Learn about first visits, treatment approaches, insurance, and more.">
  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Questions & Answers</span>
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p>Everything you need to know before your visit.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Sections -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- First Visit -->
      <div class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="faq-section__title">Your First Visit</h2>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>What should I expect during my first visit?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Your first visit includes a comprehensive consultation, examination, and discussion of your health history. We take time to understand your concerns, explain what's happening in your body, and discuss treatment options. Expect to spend about 45-60 minutes with us. You won't be rushed through a standardized protocol—your care plan will be created based on YOUR specific needs and goals.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>What should I wear to my appointment?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Wear comfortable, loose-fitting clothing that allows for movement. Athletic wear is ideal, but anything you can move comfortably in works fine. For women, it's helpful to wear or bring a sports bra for your initial examination.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Do I need to bring anything to my first appointment?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Please bring your insurance card (if using insurance), a photo ID, and any relevant medical records or imaging (X-rays, MRIs) if you have them. If another doctor referred you, bring the referral documentation. Most importantly, come prepared to discuss your health history and current concerns in detail.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Will I receive treatment on my first visit?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>In most cases, yes. After your consultation and examination, if we determine chiropractic care is appropriate for your condition, we'll typically begin gentle treatment during your first visit. However, we never pressure patients—we'll only proceed when you're comfortable and understand the treatment plan.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Treatment -->
      <div class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="faq-section__title">About Treatment</h2>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Is chiropractic care safe?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Yes, chiropractic care is very safe when performed by a licensed professional. Dr. Beyerl uses gentle techniques and adjusts his approach based on each patient's comfort level, age, and health needs. We offer both traditional and low-force adjustment options, so even patients who are nervous about "cracking" can receive effective care.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Does chiropractic treatment hurt?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Most patients find chiropractic treatment comfortable or even relaxing. You may feel some pressure during adjustments, but it shouldn't be painful. If you're sensitive or nervous, we use gentler techniques. Some patients experience mild soreness after their first few visits, similar to what you might feel after starting a new exercise routine—this typically resolves within 24-48 hours.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>How many visits will I need?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>This varies significantly based on your condition, goals, and how your body responds. Some patients feel significant relief after just a few visits, while others benefit from ongoing wellness care. We'll discuss a recommended treatment plan during your first visit, but we don't believe in creating unnecessary dependency. Our goal is to give you the tools to manage your own health long-term.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>What conditions do you treat?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>We treat a wide range of musculoskeletal conditions including back pain, neck pain, headaches, sciatica, joint pain, and postural issues. We also specialize in neuro rehabilitation for balance issues and fall prevention in adults 55 and older. Patients often tell us "I didn't know you did that!"—because what one patient needs is different from another. <a href="/conditions">View our full list of conditions we treat</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>What makes your approach different?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>We focus on calm, trust-based care that prioritizes your long-term function and independence. Unlike rushed, high-volume practices, we take time to listen, explain, and educate. We emphasize sustainable improvement rather than quick fixes or creating dependency on ongoing adjustments. We want to empower you to understand your body and take control of your own health.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Neuro Rehab -->
      <div class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="faq-section__title">Neuro Rehabilitation</h2>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>What is neuro rehabilitation?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Neuro rehabilitation (also called brain rehabilitation) focuses on improving the connection between your brain and body. It's particularly effective for balance issues, coordination problems, and fall prevention. Using specific exercises and techniques, we help retrain your nervous system to improve stability, reaction time, and overall motor function.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Who benefits from neuro rehabilitation?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Our neuro rehabilitation program is especially beneficial for adults 55 and older who want to maintain independence and reduce fall risk. It's also helpful for anyone experiencing balance issues, dizziness, coordination problems, or concerns about stability. Falls are a leading cause of injury in older adults—our program helps you stay confident and active.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>How does it reduce fall risk?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>Falls often result from a combination of factors: decreased balance, slower reaction times, reduced strength, and poor coordination. Our program addresses all of these through targeted exercises that challenge your vestibular system (inner ear balance), improve proprioception (body awareness), strengthen key muscle groups, and enhance your brain's ability to process movement information quickly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Practical Questions -->
      <div class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="faq-section__title">Practical Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Do you accept insurance?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>We accept most major insurance plans. Coverage varies by plan, so we recommend calling our office or contacting your insurance company to verify your chiropractic benefits. We're happy to help you understand your coverage and can provide documentation for out-of-network reimbursement if needed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>What are your hours?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>We're open Monday through Friday, 9am to 5pm. We try to accommodate different schedules, so if these hours don't work for you, please contact us—we may be able to arrange an alternative time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Where are you located?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>We're located at 4340 Genesee Ave, Suite 201, San Diego, CA 92117. The office is easily accessible with parking available. <a href="https://maps.google.com/?q=4340+Genesee+Ave+Suite+201+San+Diego+CA+92117" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Get directions on Google Maps</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-item__question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>How do I schedule an appointment?</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-item__answer">
              <p>You can schedule an appointment by calling us at <a href="tel:8582777500">(858) 277-7500</a>, emailing <a href="mailto:bridgechiropracticsd@gmail.com">bridgechiropracticsd@gmail.com</a>, or using our <a href="/contact">online contact form</a>. We'll get back to you within 24 hours to confirm your appointment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Still Have Questions -->
  <section class="section section--gray">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="question-cta">
        <div class="question-cta__content">
          <h2>Still Have Questions?</h2>
          <p>We're happy to answer any questions you have about our practice, your condition, or whether chiropractic care might be right for you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="question-cta__actions">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">Contact Us</a>
          <a href="tel:8582777500" class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg">Call (858) 277-7500</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Page Hero */
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--color-off-white);
    padding: 140px 0 80px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-hero p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-dark);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* FAQ Sections */
  .faq-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .faq-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .faq-section__title {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-gray-light);
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .faq-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .faq-item__question {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: none;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    transition: background var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .faq-item__question:hover {
    background: var(--color-off-white);
  }

  .faq-item__question svg {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform var(--transition-normal);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .faq-item__question[aria-expanded="true"] svg {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .faq-item__answer {
    display: none;
    padding: 0 var(--space-lg) var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .faq-item__answer p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .faq-item__answer p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .faq-item__answer a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .faq-item__answer a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .faq-item.active .faq-item__answer {
    display: block;
  }

  /* Question CTA */
  .question-cta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    padding: var(--space-3xl);
    background: var(--color-white);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .question-cta__content h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .question-cta__content p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-gray-dark);
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .question-cta__actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-hero {
      padding: 120px 0 60px;
    }

    .question-cta {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
      padding: var(--space-2xl);
    }

    .question-cta__actions {
      flex-direction: column;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .question-cta__actions .btn {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .page-hero {
      padding: 100px 0 40px;
    }

    .faq-item__question {
      padding: var(--space-md);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .faq-item__answer {
      padding: 0 var(--space-md) var(--space-md);
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // FAQ Accordion
  const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');

  faqItems.forEach(item => {
    const question = item.querySelector('.faq-item__question');

    question?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isExpanded = question.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';

      // Toggle current item
      question.setAttribute('aria-expanded', (!isExpanded).toString());
      item.classList.toggle('active');
    });
  });
</script>
